<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,790,2016]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,247]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1958,1982]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang" authorityName="Yang" box="[683,1076,1958,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guangxiensis">
<emphasis box="[683,1004,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Amblypsilopus guangxiensis</emphasis>
Yang
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter in the following features: first flagellomere nearly semicircular; arista nearly upper apical; cercus strongly curved at base; epandrium with convex apical margin. In 
<taxonomicName box="[826,1147,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guangxiensis">
<emphasis box="[826,1147,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Amblypsilopus guangxiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the first flagellomere is nearly triangular; the arista is apical; the cercus is nearly straight at base; the epandrium has an obliquely incised apical margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[318,444,222,246]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" refString="Yang, D. (1998) New species of Dolichopodidae from South China (Diptera, Dolichopodidae). Entomofauna, 19 (13), 233 - 240." type="journal article" year="1998">
Yang 
<number box="[385,444,222,246]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[455,642,222,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" refString="Yang, D., Zhang, L. L., Wang, M. Q. &amp; Zhu, Y. J. (2011) Fauna Sinica Insecta Vol. 53. Diptera Dolichopodidae. Science Press, Beijing. 1912 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[520,577,222,246]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[583,642,222,246]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
